content.text:
The issue was a regression in the pagination of the "Prompts responses list". When viewing all responses for a prompt, new posts would load once or twice and then stop, and posts would shift places.

This behavior is characteristic of a mismatch between the pagination cursor used by the client and the sorting order used by the API. The Reader uses `date_tagged` for sorting and pagination cursor (`before` parameter) for tag streams (detected by `isTagTopic()`). However, the API likely uses `date_published` (or simple `date`) for sorting and pagination for these prompt tags.

If `date_tagged` is slightly different from `date_published` (e.g. later), requesting posts `before=date_tagged` might return posts that are already loaded (because their `date_published` < `date_tagged`). This causes the client to receive duplicate posts, which are updated in the local database but don't increase the list size, causing pagination to stall. It also explains the "shifting" as the local list is re-sorted or updated.

The fix involves forcing the usage of `date_published` for sorting and pagination for tags related to blogging prompts (`dailyprompt` and `bloganuary`). This is done by modifying `ReaderPostTable.getSortColumnForTag` to check if the tag slug starts with `dailyprompt` or `bloganuary`, and if so, returning `date_published` instead of `date_tagged`, even if it is identified as a tag topic.

I modified `WordPress/src/main/java/org/wordpress/android/datasets/ReaderPostTable.java` to implement this exception.

```java
    private static String getSortColumnForTag(ReaderTag tag) {
        if (tag.isPostsILike()) {
            return "date_liked";
        } else if (tag.isFollowedSites()) {
            return "date_published";
        } else if (tag.tagType == ReaderTagType.SEARCH) {
            return "score";
        } else if (tag.isTagTopic() || tag.isBookmarked()) {
            if (tag.getTagSlug().startsWith("dailyprompt") || tag.getTagSlug().startsWith("bloganuary")) {
                return "date_published";
            }
            return "date_tagged";
        } else {
            return "date_published";
        }
    }
```

